<br>
Clearly the poster of the above has not ever played a wizard nor knows much about them.  And thus should not really be posted such....<br>
<br>
To clarify: while a wizard can, with maximum crit AA's, get almost 1 in 4 crit hits (current parsings seem to show about a 23% crit rate) this requires a CLASS AA (which you cant even start to get til you are 59) and a POP AA which has a pre-requisit of the 59th AA. In total max crit AA's also cost you 42 AA's - how many 55th level chars have that many I wonder?<br>
<br>
Therefore the above statement is totally false.<br>
<br>
As for doing a 3000 crit - the highest damage spell a 55th wizard has is the 1150 Ice Comet (and they'd be mad to use this often as it is hopelessly inneficient and gets resisted often). Even with an ID3 item hitting for the full 20% extra and a bard with rizlona's you're not going to get many (in relality probably any) crits over 3000. And they'd go OOM very rapidly. <br>
<br>
Please get your facts straight before posting. <p>------------------<br>
